-- Colombia Stock Movers: Bolsa de Valores, Pacific Rubiales Energy
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2012-02-23T22:15:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-23/colombia-stock-movers-bolsa-de-valores-pacific-rubiales-energy.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  rose 2.4 percent to 14,921.95, while the
Colcap Index gained 1 percent to 1,720.51.  Bolsa de Valores de Colombia SA  (BVC CB), the operator of
 Colombia ’s main stock exchange, rose 2.8 percent to 32.9 pesos,
a three-month high. The company will pay a 2012 dividend of 1.52
pesos per share, including an extraordinary dividend of 0.46
pesos per share, according to a regulatory filing today. That is
a 64 percent increase from last year’s dividend, the filing
said.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in Colombia, rose 7.4 percent
to 52,280 pesos, a nine-month high. Oil and natural-gas reserves
at the end of last year were 52 percent higher than the year
before, driven by an 83 percent exploration success rate,
according to a statement on the company’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
